---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import ButtonLink from "../components/ButtonLink.astro";
import WaveDivider from "../components/WaveDivider.astro";
import { lanes } from "../data/lanes";
import ExperienceRow from "../components/ExperienceRow.astro";
import { experience } from "../data/experience";

const mainExperience = experience.filter((e) => !e.background);
const backgroundExperience = experience.filter((e) => e.background);

const buildingNow = [
  "Finishing this portfolio and publishing fuller case studies as the work is ready",
  "Building SEA32, a Python and DuckDB simulation for a hypothetical Seattle NBA expansion roster",
  "Applying for business, marketing, and analytics roles",
  "Helping with listing content while planning local SEO and analytics for my family's real estate business",
  "Keeping up my Japanese, with JLPT N3 as the longer-term goal",
];
---

<Base
  title="About · Clark Hayashi"
  description="Business Analytics and Marketing graduate from Seattle University, rooted in Hawai‘i. Analytics, marketing measurement, AI workflows, operations, and visual communication."
>
  <article class="about-page mx-auto px-6 pb-10 pt-10 md:pt-16">
    <!-- Intro -->
    <section class="about-intro" aria-labelledby="about-title">
      <h1
        id="about-title"
        class="about-title font-serif text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight md:text-5xl"
      >
        About
      </h1>

      <p class="about-hello text-lg text-ink/80">Hi, I'm Clark Hayashi.</p>

      <figure class="about-portrait">
        <img
          src="/images/headshot-cutout.svg"
          alt="Clark Hayashi in a navy suit"
          width="585"
          height="640"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </figure>

      <div class="about-copy space-y-5 leading-relaxed text-ink/80">
        <p>
          I'm a Business Analytics and Marketing graduate from Seattle University
          with a minor in Japanese, originally from Hawai‘i. My background blends
          analytics, marketing, AI, operations, global study, sports leadership,
          visual communication, and service. Most of it comes down to the
          same move: taking something messy (a dataset, a process, a pile of
          competing ideas) and turning it into something a team can act on.
        </p>

        <p>
          At Bank of Hawaii, as one of the bank's first AI interns, that meant
          interviewing people across the organization about where AI could
          actually help, then building the scoring framework and Power BI
          dashboard leadership used to prioritize the opportunities. The rest of
          the record is below. One note from four years of refereeing flag
          football: it teaches you more about making fast calls with incomplete
          information than most classrooms do.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="about-body">
    <!-- Professional lanes -->
    <section class="mt-14">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">What I Bring</h2>
      <div class="mt-6">
        {
          lanes.map((lane) => (
            <div class="border-t border-ink/10 py-5">
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold tracking-tight">
                {lane.title}
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-1 leading-relaxed text-ink/70">{lane.description}</p>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Experience snapshot -->
    <section class="mt-14">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Experience Snapshot
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-ink/70">
        The full picture. The <a
          href="/resume.pdf"
          class="font-medium text-teal-deep transition-colors hover:text-ink">resume</a
        > is the one-page version.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6">
        {mainExperience.map((item) => <ExperienceRow item={item} />)}
      </div>

      <details class="group mt-8">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer list-none text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-bark transition-colors hover:text-teal-deep">
          <span class="group-open:hidden">Background · sports, culture &amp; first jobs ({backgroundExperience.length} more) ↓</span>
          <span class="hidden group-open:inline">Background ↑</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="mt-4">
          {backgroundExperience.map((item) => <ExperienceRow item={item} />)}
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>

    <WaveDivider />

    <!-- Rooted Perspective -->
    <section class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Rooted Perspective
      </h2>
      <div class="mt-5 space-y-5 leading-relaxed text-ink/80">
        <p>
          I grew up in Hawai‘i, where community isn't a value statement; it's
          just how things get done. Seattle is where I learned to work:
          analytics and marketing classes, a student credit union, four years
          of intramural sports. A semester at Sophia University in Tokyo and a
          study tour through Tuscany stretched that further. Being the person
          who doesn't fully speak the language or know the customs teaches you
          to pay close attention.
        </p>
        <p>
          Sports run through all of it: co-captaining my high school varsity
          basketball team, officiating and managing intramural leagues, and
          scrimmaging against a D1 women's basketball team as a practice
          player. None of this shows up on a dashboard, but it shapes how I
          build one. I ask who will actually use the thing, I over-communicate
          rather than assume, and I finish what I start, a habit Scouting
          drilled in early. The question underneath every project stays the
          same: how do I make this clearer, more useful, and more human?
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 md:grid-cols-4 md:gap-4">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/images/hawaii/hawaii-coast.jpg"
            alt="Coastline in Hawai‘i with mountains meeting the ocean"
            class="aspect-[4/5] w-full rounded-lg object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
            width="480"
            height="600"
          />
          <figcaption class="mt-2 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-bark">
            Hawai‘i
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/images/seattle/seattle-space-needle.jpg"
            alt="Seattle skyline with the Space Needle from Gas Works Park"
            class="aspect-[4/5] w-full rounded-lg object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
            width="480"
            height="600"
          />
          <figcaption class="mt-2 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-bark">
            Seattle
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/images/japan/tokyo-skytree-dusk.jpg"
            alt="Tokyo skyline with the Skytree at dusk"
            class="aspect-[4/5] w-full rounded-lg object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
            width="480"
            height="600"
          />
          <figcaption class="mt-2 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-bark">
            Tokyo
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/images/italy/tuscan-vineyards.jpg"
            alt="Vineyard hills in the Italian countryside at golden hour"
            class="aspect-[4/5] w-full rounded-lg object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
            width="480"
            height="600"
          />
          <figcaption class="mt-2 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-bark">
            Italy
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <a
        href="/journey"
        class="mt-6 inline-block font-medium text-teal-deep transition-colors hover:text-ink"
        >Trace the whole journey on the globe →</a
      >
    </section>

    <!-- What I'm building now -->
    <section class="mt-14">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        What I'm Working On Now
      </h2>
      <ul class="mt-5 space-y-2.5">
        {
          buildingNow.map((item) => (
            <li class="flex gap-3 leading-relaxed text-ink/75">
              <span class="mt-2.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-teal" aria-hidden="true" />
              {item}
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <div class="mt-14 border-t border-ink/10 pt-10">
      <p class="max-w-[58ch] text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink/75">
        I'm looking for roles where analytics, practical judgment, and clear
        communication all matter. If that sounds like your team, I'd love to
        talk.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <ButtonLink href="mailto:hayashiclark@gmail.com">Email me</ButtonLink>
        <ButtonLink
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/clark-hayashi"
          variant="ghost"
          external>LinkedIn</ButtonLink
        >
        <ButtonLink href="/resume.pdf" variant="ghost">Resume</ButtonLink>
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <style>
    .about-page {
      width: min(78rem, 100%);
    }

    .about-intro {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-areas:
        "title portrait"
        "hello portrait"
        "copy portrait";
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(17rem, 0.48fr);
      column-gap: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 5.5rem);
      align-items: start;
    }

    .about-title {
      grid-area: title;
    }

    .about-hello {
      grid-area: hello;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }

    .about-copy {
      grid-area: copy;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }

    .about-portrait {
      grid-area: portrait;
      align-self: end;
      margin: 0;
    }

    .about-portrait img {
      display: block;
      width: min(100%, 24rem);
      height: auto;
      margin-inline: auto 0;
    }

    .about-body {
      max-width: 72ch;
    }

    @media (max-width: 767px) {
      .about-intro {
        grid-template-areas:
          "title"
          "hello"
          "portrait"
          "copy";
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
      }

      .about-hello {
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
      }

      .about-portrait {
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
      }

      .about-portrait img {
        width: min(78vw, 18rem);
        margin-inline: auto;
      }

      .about-copy {
        margin-top: 2rem;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Base>
